Description

AlgorithmApp
AlgorithmApp is a JFrame subclass that provides an interactive user interface for managing, learning, and deleting Rubik's Cube algorithms.

AlgorithmCollection class provides functionality to manage a collection of algorithms.
AlgorithmCollectionTest
 
AlgorithmCube
AlgorithmCube class allows the user to learn and practice a specific algorithm on the Rubik's Cube.

BackgroundPanel is a custom JPanel subclass that displays an image as its background.
Cube
Represents a Rubik's Cube and provides methods for rotating, drawing and checking the solved state.

Cubie
Represents a cubie (small cube) of a Rubik's cube with an associated position, faces, and a solved position.

Represents a face of a cube with an associated color, id, and facing direction.

GergosCube class is the main class to run the Rubik's Cube simulation.

Represents a LogReader that reads logs from a file.

Represents a LogViewer that displays logs from a LogReader.
LogWriter
Represents a LogWriter that writes logs to a file.
MainApp
MainApp is the entry point for the Gergos Cube application.
Move
Move class represents a single move of the Rubik's Cube.

OldPochmanCollection
OldPochmanCollection class provides functionality to manage a collection of Old Pochman algorithms.

RGBInputPanel
RGBInputPanel is a JPanel subclass that provides an input interface for RGB values.
RubiksCubeLogic
The RubiksCubeLogic class represents the core logic for solving a Rubik's Cube using the Old Pochmann method.
Settings
Settings is a class responsible for managing the application settings, including loading and saving them to a JSON file.
SettingsApp
SettingsApp is a class responsible for managing and displaying the settings of the Gergos Cube application.
